OL,3,C#140 million revamp for railway
OL,4,Cstation gets go-ahead
OL,6,FPlans to revamp Wales' busiest railway
OL,7,Fstation have got the go-ahead from the
OL,8,FUK Government.
OL,10,F#140 million will be spent to improve
OL,11,FCardiff Central Station. The
OL,12,FDepartment for Transport has approved
OL,13,F#77 million for the project, with an
OL,14,Fadditional #40 million from Cardiff
OL,15,FCapital Region City Deal and #21
OL,16,Fmillion from the Welsh Government.
OL,18,FThe plans include changes to the
OL,19,Fsouthern entrance at the car park, a
OL,20,Flarger main concourse, and extending
OL,21,FPlatform 0 to increase capacity.
